The '''Coastal Volcanic Belt''' (CVB) is a major [[Late Silurian]] [[volcanic belt]] extending from [[Massachusetts]], [[United States]] into southwestern [[New Brunswick]], [[Canada]]. It is one of the largest [[Bimodal volcanism|bimodal volcanic]] provinces in world, ranging from [[basalt]]s to [[rhyolite]]s.<ref>[http://gsa.confex.com/gsa/2001NE/finalprogram/abstract_2376.htm The Coastal Volcanic Belt (CVB), Easternmost Maine: Geochemistry And Tectonic Setting]</ref>
==See also== {{Portal|Volcanism of Canada}} *[[Volcanism of Canada]] *[[Volcanism of Eastern Canada]]
==External links== *[http://www.livescience.com/40847-maine-supervolcanoes-found.html Maine's Volcanoes (Yes, Maine) Among World's Biggest]
